column2: The UK's Safest Places to Live

For most, being home means being safe - but that means you've got to think ahead when buying property. Bad weather, crime, and fast medical response time are all something you want to watch out for when picking where you want to live. But with this guide, the work is already done for you - have a look to see the safest places to find a home.
The UK's Safest Places to Live | CompareTheMarket
Home should feel safe, so you have to think ahead when buying property. Use our guide to have a look at the safest property locations to find a home.

All crime stats refer to February 2018 in city centres. London has used an average of several central locations as representative. Burglary and robbery are differentiated by burglary specifically referring to illegal entrance to a structure in order to perpetrate the theft, while robbery uses fear or force to take personal property. Crime rates are not available for Scotland in the same structure and thus the annual figure has been divided into months to provide context.

A&E waiting times are not available in the same structure for Northern Ireland as in other locations and therefore have been excluded.

Doctors per person is measured by country within the UK and North East England (sourced from a comparison point).

Ambulance response times have used the city centre as a representative figure.

House prices have been drawn from the average sale price of houses in city centres in December 2017 on Rightmove.co.uk.

Average days of thunder have been given an average between the two data brackets available.
